.INDENT 2.0
.INDENT 3.5
Will use the behaviour of the 2014.1 branch and earlier.
.sp
Overwrites elements according the order in which they are processed.
.sp
First pillar processed:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
A:
  first_key: blah
  second_key: blah
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Second pillar processed:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
A:
  third_key: blah
  fourth_key: blah
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
will be merged as:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
A:
  third_key: blah
  fourth_key: blah
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.IP \(bu 2
smart (default):
.INDENT 2.0
.INDENT 3.5
Guesses the best strategy based on the "renderer" setting.
