.sp
The map that comes from a pillar cannot be directly consumed by the env option.
To use it one must convert it to a list. Example:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
printenv:
  cmd.run:
    \- env:
      {% for key, value in pillar[\(aqkeys\(aq].iteritems() %}
      \- \(aq{{ key }}\(aq: \(aq{{ value }}\(aq
      {% endfor %}
.ft P
.fi
